:\"What Type of Establishments Are Eligible?\";s:4:\"body\";s:261:\"Hospitality establishments such as hotels, restaurants, resorts, casinos, country clubs, retirement communities, airlines, peer-to-peer lodging, theme parks, water parks, hospitality schools, bed and breakfasts, and others may be considered for the Julian Star.\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916711860;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:27:\"Criteria for Establishments\";s:4:\"body\";s:399:\"To be considered for the Julian Star, the establishment must be able to consistently deliver superlative customer service. Customer service must be timely, efficient, responsive, connective, and resonant. Customer service delivery will be measured using feedback from current and previous customers, verifiable online reviews, and verifiable narratives from current or former hospitality associates.\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916734655;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:16:\"Assessment Areas\";s:4:\"body\";s:272:\"Establishments will be judged in the following areas:\r\n*Overall service personality of the establishment * Quality of service interaction * Responsiveness of staff * Compassionate and service-orientation of staff * Friendliness of staff * Problem resolution and follow-up.\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916754937;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:14:\"On-site Visits\";s:4:\"body\";s:539:\"In some instances, an IHI or AHI representative may visit the establishment to conduct direct observation of how customer service is delivered to customers.\r\n\r\nOn-site reviewers will rate:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Mastery of service technique</li>\r\n 	<li>Creativity of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Responsiveness/timeliness of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Intuitive skills of staff members</li>\r\n 	<li>Consistency of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Emotive problem resolution skills of staff members</li>\r\n 	<li>Compassion in service</li>\r\n 	<li>Active listening skills</li>\r\n</ol>\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916775392;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:56:\"Which Individuals or Hospitality Positions Are Eligible?\";s:4:\"body\";s:122:\"Hospitality professionals working in management and hourly positions worldwide are eligible to earn the Julian Star award.\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916787091;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:24:\"Criteria for Individuals\";s:4:\"body\";s:489:\"<ul>\r\n 	<li>Nominees must be able to demonstrate customer service exceptionalism.</li>\r\n 	<li>The award committee will take into consideration the community service efforts of nominees.</li>\r\n 	<li>Nominees who are managers must demonstrate not only exceptional customer service skills, they should also demonstrate service leadership, team leadership, and a servant leadership approach. Who has the nominee developed to be a service leader? How does the nominee lead the team?</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916806844;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:16:\"Assessment Areas\";s:4:\"body\";s:331:\"Individuals will be judged in the following areas:\r\n* Overall service personality * Documented examples of exceptional customer service * Customer narratives * Team member and/or supervisor feedback * Problem resolution skills.\r\nShortlisted nominees may be invited to participate in a video interview or respond to a questionnaire.\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916828694;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:14:\"On-site Visits\";s:4:\"body\";s:545:\"In some instances, an IHI or AHI representative may visit the establishment where the nominee works to observe and judge the nominee’s interactions with customers. On-site reviewers will rate:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Mastery of service technique</li>\r\n 	<li>Creativity of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Responsiveness/timeliness of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Intuitive skills of staff members</li>\r\n 	<li>Consistency of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Emotive problem resolution skills of staff members</li>\r\n 	<li>Compassion in service</li>\r\n 	<li>Active listening skills</li>\r\n</ol>\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916846277;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:28:\"Julian Award for Restaurants\";s:4:\"body\";s:1052:\"The Julian Star Award for restaurants follows the same general guidelines as the award for other hospitality entities, however, the J Star for restaurants will emphasize site visits. More often than not, anonymous reviewers from IHI or AHI will visit the restaurant and create a detailed report about their customer service experience. The report will be shared with IHI’s or AHI’s full review committee, after which a decision will be made whether the restaurant has earned the Julian Star or not.\r\n\r\nOn-site reviewers will rate:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Mastery of service technique</li>\r\n 	<li>Creativity of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Responsiveness/timeliness of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Intuitive skills of staff members</li>\r\n 	<li>Consistency of service</li>\r\n 	<li>Emotive problem resolution skills of staff members</li>\r\n 	<li>Compassion in service</li>\r\n 	<li>Active listening skills</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nReviewers will not rate:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Food quality</li>\r\n 	<li>Food presentation</li>\r\n 	<li>Ambience</li>\r\n 	<li>Table Setting</li>\r\n 	<li>Value of food</li>\r\n</ol>\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916863056;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:6:\"Judges\";s:4:\"body\";s:252:\"Our judges are highly accomplished veterans of the hospitality industry. To protect them from the behind-the-scenes lobbying and pandering that typically accompanies coveted awards such as the Julian Star, the judges’ names will be kept confidential.\";s:4:\"hide\";s:5:\"false\";s:11:\"hide_schema\";s:5:\"false\";}i:1595916879200;a:4:{s:6:\"header\";s:11:\"Nominations\";s:4:\"body\";s:737:\"Open call-to-entry starts in October o