 core areas as the zones in which a hospitality practitioner must operate in order to demonstrate service leadership.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"27\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\" el_class=\"who-we-img\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section parallax=\"content-moving\" parallax_image=\"31\" el_class=\"welcome-head mission-sec zones-sec\" css=\".vc_custom_1595926878922{margin-right: 0px !important;margin-left: 0px !important;padding-top: 60px !important;padding-right: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 60px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}\"][vc_row el_class=\"container align-center\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text el_class=\"welcome-head-white\"]\r\n<h2>Zones</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner equal_height=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\" css=\".vc_custom_1595847985841{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595926449408{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\" el_class=\"certification-points\"]\r\n<ul class=\"pointed-finger chevron-arrow\">\r\n 	<li>Humility Zone</li>\r\n 	<li>Compassion Zone</li>\r\n 	<li>Stamina Zone</li>\r\n 	<li>Consistency Zone</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595926458515{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\" el_class=\"certification-points\"]\r\n<ul class=\"pointed-finger chevron-arrow\">\r\n 	<li>Accountability Zone</li>\r\n 	<li>Recognition Zone</li>\r\n 	<li>Intuition Zone</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595926465378{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\" el_class=\"certification-points\"]\r\n<ul class=\"pointed-finger chevron-arrow\">\r\n 	<li>Creativity Zone</li>\r\n 	<li>Urgency Zone</li>\r\n 	<li>Active Listening Zone</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner equal_height=\"yes\" css=\".vc_custom_1595926977174{padding-top: 25px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner css=\".vc_custom_1595847985841{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595926829728{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\" el_class=\"certification-points\"]The Julian Star award is founded on the 10Z Model. In addition to the 10Z Model, AHI also encourages hospitality companies and leaders to adopt the BITTER Model (also developed by Jeffrey O) to help improve customer service outcomes.\r\n\r\nAccording to Jeffrey O, “Exceptional customer service is the art of making the impossible possible. A great hospitalitarian is a magician, a comedian, and a therapist, all rolled into one.”[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section el_class=\"who-we-are-sec\"][vc_row el_class=\"container align-center\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner equal_height=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1595847985841{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595927927244{margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-right: 35px !important;}\"]\r\n<h2><b>THE BITTER MODEL</b></h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595927844862{margin-bottom: 15px !important;padding-right: 35px !important;}\"]\r\n<h4 class=\"mar-tp-10\">The Bitter truth about how leaders should promote customer satisfaction in their organizations</h4>\r\nThe BITTER model focuses on six critical actions that hospitality leaders should implement to promote a positive customer service culture within the enterprise.\r\n<div class=\"bitter-sec\">\r\n<p class=\"bitter-content\"><strong>BENCHMARK</strong> customer satisfaction. Set departmental customer service goals.</p>\r\n<p class=\"bitter-content\"><strong>INCENT</strong> your teams using positive feedback, recognition programs, and a visualization of what success looks like.</p>\r\n<p class=\"bitter-content\"><strong>TRAIN</strong> your staff on customer service best practices. Use role play, team activities, games, and behavior modeling.</p>\r\n<p class=\"bitter-content\"><strong>TRANSLATE</strong> your customer service goals into a simple language that your team can understand. Define the objective, the strategy, and help each team member gain an answer to the question: “what is in it for me?”</p>\r\n<p class=\"bitter-content\"><strong>EMPOWER</strong> your team to take ownership of problems, and to resolve problems creatively, compassionately, and timely.</p>\r\n<p class=\"bitter-content\"><strong>REINFORCE</strong> accountability using customer feedback, performance reviews, checklists, coaching, mentoring, and counseling.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"25\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\" el_class=\"who-we-img\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]','SERVICE LEADERSHIP','','publish','closed','closed','','service-leadership','','','2020-07-28 09:18:49','2020-07-28 09:18:49','',0,'http://188.166.160.223/american/?page_id=213',0,'page','',0),(215,1,'2020-07-28 07:29:11','2020-07-28 07:29:11','[vc_section el_class=\"who-we-are-sec\"][vc_row el_class=\"container align-center\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner equal_height=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\" css=\".vc_custom_1595847985841{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1595851229913{margin-bottom: 15px !important;padding-right: 35px !important;}\"]The American Hospitality Institute offers training and certifications to hotel leaders in various disciplines.\r\nTraining and testing are available for the certifications listed below. Applicants must achieve a minimum score of 70% on the certification exam. The cost of each certification is $500. To apply, or to see if you qualify, click on the link for the certification that you are interested in.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=